1️⃣ What is JSON?

JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) is a lightweight format used to store and transfer data between client and server.

👉 It looks like a JavaScript object, but it is always a string when transferred over network

📦 Example JSON
{
  "name": "Naveen",
  "age": 20,
  "skills": ["Java", "Node.js"]
}
⚙️ 2️⃣ JSON vs JavaScript Object
JSON	JavaScript Object
String format	Actual object
Used in network	Used in code
Keys must be in quotes	Quotes optional
🔄 3️⃣ Conversion (Very Important 🔥)
🔹 1. Object → JSON String

👉 Use JSON.stringify()

const obj = {
  name: "Naveen",
  age: 20
};

const jsonString = JSON.stringify(obj);

console.log(jsonString);

👉 Output:

{"name":"Naveen","age":20}
🔹 2. JSON String → Object

👉 Use JSON.parse()

const jsonString = '{"name":"Naveen","age":20}';

const obj = JSON.parse(jsonString);

console.log(obj.name);

👉 Output:

Naveen
🌐 4️⃣ JSON in Request–Response (Real Use)
📤 Sending JSON (Server → Client)
const http = require('http');

http.createServer((req, res) => {
    const data = { name: "Naveen", role: "Developer" };

    res.setHeader("Content-Type", "application/json");
    res.end(JSON.stringify(data));
}).listen(3000);
📥 Receiving JSON (Client → Server)
let body = '';

req.on('data', chunk => {
    body += chunk;
});

req.on('end', () => {
    const data = JSON.parse(body);
    console.log(data);
});
🚀 5️⃣ JSON with Express (Easy Way 🔥)
Enable JSON parsing middleware
app.use(express.json());
Example
app.post('/user', (req, res) => {
    console.log(req.body); // already parsed JSON
    res.send("Data received");
});
🎯 6️⃣ Interview Questions + Answers
Q1: What is JSON?

👉 A lightweight data format used for data exchange between client and server.

Q2: How to convert object to JSON string?

👉 Using JSON.stringify()

Q3: How to convert JSON string to object?

👉 Using JSON.parse()

Q4: Why do we convert JSON to string?

👉 Because data over network is transferred as string format

Q5: What is Content-Type for JSON?

👉

application/json
Q6: What happens if JSON.parse() gets invalid data?

👉 It throws an error (SyntaxError)

Q7: Difference between JSON and JavaScript object?

👉 JSON is string format, object is in-memory structure
